  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>Hey I made a proof of concept over here:<br>
<a href="https://github.com/micwallace/zxing">https://github.com/micwallace/zxing</a></p>

<p>It adds a few files to the project,<br>
1. com.google.zxing.client.android.HttpServer (serves the barcode text and bitmaps in base 64)<br>
2. com.google.zxing.client.android.HttpServerUI (activity to start server, better integration needed)<br>
3. layout files &amp; a few values<br>
4. A html example app with javascript (no hosting needed, just open it up).</p>

<p>I also migrated the android parts of the project into their own project and added gradle build environment.</p>

<p>It works pretty well with a nice stream of images in the browser, some optimization is needed though, for instance, I am using separate http calls for each frame! A better solution would be to use a single stream. Also there's none of your awesome barcode detection overlays.</p>

<p>The problem is it's not detecting barcodes, it would be awesome if you could please take a look at com.google.zxing.client.android.HttpServer (from line 151) and see if I'm calling the decode library in the right way?</p>

<p>Once it's optimised and reading barcodes it'll be the perfect framework for a nice looking jquery widget.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
